cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR 

Reasoning: The paper deals with 3D multi-object understanding from 2D single shot images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses object-oriented data association and probabilistic simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM), which are topics in robotics and control. Hence, cs.RO (Robotics) is the second likely category. The paper uses variational auto-encoder (VAE) for estimating latent variables, which is a machine learning technique. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper was submitted to the arXiv Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) conference, which suggests that cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely category.
